# Executive Summary

A credential dumping attack was detected involving the use of **Mimikatz** to access the Windows LSASS process and attempt extraction of authentication material from memory.

The attack was identified through **Sysmon Event ID 10 (Process Access)** logs collected by Winlogbeat and analyzed within the Elastic Stack SIEM environment. Detection occurred within seconds of execution, allowing rapid containment and investigation.

